<article>
    <h1>Film&#xAD;ing com&#xAD;pleted for Chi&#xAD;nese TV adap&#xAD;ta&#xAD;tion of The Three-Body Prob&#xAD;lem</h1>
    <h2></h2>
    <section>
        <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/textview" title="The Straits Times">The Straits Times</a>
        - <a href="/singapore/the-straits-times/20201216/textview" title="The Straits Times - 2020-12-16"><time>2020-12-16</time></a>
        - <span>LIFE | TRENDING</span>
        - <span role="byline"></span>
    </section>

    <p>• Film­ing has been com­pleted for Three­Body, a live-ac­tion tele­vi­sion adap­ta­tion of Chi­nese au­thor Liu Cixin’s Hugo Award-win­ning sci­ence-fic­tion novel, The Three-Body Prob­lem.</p>
    <p>The show made the an­nounce­ment on its of­fi­cial Weibo ac­count on Mon­day by re­leas­ing a pro­mo­tional video, which did not spec­ify the date of re­lease.</p>
    <p>It said film­ing took about six months, with the Chi­nese series’ de­vel­op­ment be­gin­ning more than four years ago. The Three-Body Prob­lem (2008) is the first book of Liu’s tril­ogy Re­mem­brance Of Earth’s Past, which re­volves around Chi­nese physi­cist Ye Wen­jie’s con­tact with the Triso­larans, an alien civil­i­sa­tion that ex­ists in a three-sun sys­tem, and the cen­turies-long clashes that fol­low be­tween earth­lings and the aliens.</p>
    <p>The sec­ond and third books in the tril­ogy are The Dark For­est (2008) and Death’s End (2010) re­spec­tively. Chi­nese ac­tress Olivia Wang plays the younger ver­sion of Ye, while the older ver­sion of the physi­cist is played by ac­tress Chen Jin.</p>
    <p>The 24-episode series, which also stars Ed­ward Zhang and Yu Hewei, is di­rected by Yang Lei.</p>
    <p>In 2015, Liu be­came the first Asian writer to win the pres­ti­gious Hugo Award for Best Novel for The Three-Body Prob­lem.</p>
    <p>An an­i­mated adap­ta­tion of the novel, an­nounced last year as a project by Chi­nese on­line video shar­ing plat­form Bili­bili, is sched­uled for re­lease next year.</p>
    <p>Stream­ing gi­ant Netflix also an­nounced in Septem­ber that it was adapt­ing the novel into an English-lan­guage tele­vi­sion series helmed by Game Of Thrones showrun­ners David Be­nioff and D.B. Weiss.</p>
    <p>The Wan­der­ing Earth, a sci­ence-fic­tion short story by Liu, 57, was turned into a block­buster film last year that gen­er­ated a box-of­fice rev­enue of 4.68 bil­lion yuan (S$954.5 mil­lion) in China.</p>
    <p>Its se­quel, The Wan­der­ing Earth II, is set for re­lease in 2023, ac­cord­ing to an an­nounce­ment made last month.</p>

